K3K3-NONARROWING is an NP-complete problem that asks whether a given graph has a red/blue edge-coloring such that there are no red K3's and no blue K3's. The NP-hardness proof of this problem relies on a special graph called a K3K3-sender: a graph G with "sender edges" e and f such that e and f are distinct and e has the same color as f in all K3K3-good colorings of G.
